review:
straight up the best total war game to date, played it hundreds of hours years ago and i still would if it ran better in modern systems, it may lack the flashy graphics and fancy animations of the newest entries in the series, but it makes up for it in gameplay, with the best individual, unit to unit and formation combat interactions out of all the games (and this game came out in 2004!)

some people prefer medieval 2, but it's buggy and unfinished, that along with some changes made to the game that i do not agree with make me prefer the original rome. that being said, medieval 2 runs a lot better than rome in modern systems.

if you can get over how dated the game looks and feels, you're in for a great time (with access to a ton of mods too!)

One of the best strategy games and the best part of the "Total War" series. Epic-scale game with endless replayability!

Briefly, "Rome: Total War" is:
- Development of cities and armies;
- Unique buildings and armies for each nation;
- Epic battles and in-depth diplomacy;
- Generals and thousands of soldiers;
- Espionage, assassinations and bribery;
- Family tree and weddings;
- One of the best eras in history!

9/10

